{"id":73695,"title":"Therapeutic mammaplasty.","abstract":"Therapeutic mammaplasty is a term for the oncoplastic application of breast reduction and mastopexy techniques to treat selected breast tumours by breast conserving surgery (BCS). It has the potential to increase the indications for BCS as well as achieve more acceptable aesthetic results from it in suitable women. Now an established technique in the range of oncoplastic options for women with breast cancer, it finds common application and is associated with good oncological and quality of life outcomes.","date":"2014-06-04","categories":"Neoplasms","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24889526","annotations":[{"name":"Breast cancer","weight":0.816298,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Breast_cancer"},{"name":"Cancer","weight":0.804197,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer"},{"name":"Oncology","weight":0.773888,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oncology"},{"name":"Tumor","weight":0.756683,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tumor"},{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.750806,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Surgery","weight":0.728515,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Surgery"},{"name":"Breast","weight":0.663323,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Breast"},{"name":"Mastopexy","weight":0.592932,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mastopexy"},{"name":"Breast reduction","weight":0.558458,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Breast_reduction"},{"name":"Aesthetics","weight":0.200374,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aesthetics"},{"name":"Quality of life","weight":0.172891,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quality_of_life"},{"name":"Mammaplasty","weight":0.152918,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mammaplasty"},{"name":"Redox","weight":0.127776,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Redox"},